PRETORIA - There were scenes of anger and clashes on Friday when hundreds of people made their way through the Pretoria city centre, protesting against illegal immigrants. The march comes amid attacks on foreign nationals in Pretoria West and other townships in the capital.Residents attribute social ills and high unemployment rates to illegal immigrants.Government says it is working to ensure a peaceful march.Follow eNCA's live blog below throughout the day for updates on the protests. eNCA